cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on vision-based sign language recognition and proposes deep learning models for word-level sign recognition.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper deals with language in the context of sign language recognition.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes deep learning models for sign recognition.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper aims to help hearing-impaired people to communicate with others.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with video datasets and proposes methods for analyzing human pose trajectories.
